Pour @salted water{300%ml} into a #pot.

Stir in the @Jasmine Rice{150%g} and bring to the boil. Lower heat to medium,
cover and cook for ~{12%minutes}.

Remove from the heat. Keep covered for ~{12%minutes} or until ready to serve
(the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Halve the @Bell Pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips.

Halve and peel the @Onion{1}. Cut each half into three wedges. Roughly chop
the @Coriander{5%g}(roughly chopped, stalks and all).

Drain the @Tofu{280%g} and chop into 2cm cubes. Pat dry with #kitchen paper.
In a #bowl, toss the tofu cubes with the @Soy Sauce{1%sachet}.

Place a pan over high heat with a drizzle of @oil{}.

Once hot, fry the tofu until slightly crispy, shifting frequently to ensure it
doesn't burn, ~{6-8%minutes}.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Remove from the pan and set aside.

Return the pan to medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{}.

Fry the onion and pepper until softened, stirring occasionally, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Stir in the @Ketjap Manis{2%sachets}, @Red Wine Vinegar{2%sachets},
@Tomato Paste{1%tin} and @water{100%ml}.

Simmer until sauce has thickened, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Once thickened, add the tofu and @sugar{2%tsp} to the pan. Season to taste
with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> TIP: Add a splash of water if you feel the sauce is too thick.

Serve the the rice in deep #bowls{}.

Top with the sweet and sour tofu.

Garnish with @Cashews{20%g} and chopped coriander.